parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leaks from Front Cylinder Bank Valve Cover Gasket
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks from the front cylinder bank valve cover gasket can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, oil leaks can damage other engine components, such as the alternator, resulting in costly repairs.
Inadequate recall repairs can lead to recurring oil leaks, engine stalling, and damage to other engine components, resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The unavailability of recall parts can delay or prevent necessary repairs, leaving vehicles on the road with potential safety hazards, such as oil leaks and engine stalling.
